<div class="row">
  <br>
</div>
<div style="background-color:transparent">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="twelve columns left" style="padding-top:2em;padding-bottom:2em">
      <h1 id='site-title'>Ruby Programming <small>Heroku Registry</small></h1>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="four columns">
    <div class="panel radius" style="background-color:#ff8">
      <h4>Link to Your App</h4>
      <p>Use this form to enter the URL for your Ruby Programming Heroku Rails Application. This form is collecting URLs from both of my Ruby courses at <a href="http://hackingthevalley.com/ccsf/ruby">City College of San Francisco</a> and
      <a href="http://hackingthevalley.com/csm/ruby">College of San Mateo.</a></p>
        <p>Enter your USERID and your HEROKU app.</p>
      <p>Read the <a href="/welcome/assignment">assignment</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="eight columns" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;">
      <h3>Register your Heroku URL</h3>
      <%= form_for @student, :url => {:action => 'create'} do |f| %>
          <p><%= f.label :COURSE %></p>
          <p><%= f.select :course, options_for_select(['Choose your course',['CS 132A','cs132a'],['CIS 113','cis113']]) %></p>
          <p><%= f.label :USERID %></p>
          <p><%= f.text_field :name, :placeholder =>'Your USERID' %></p>
          <p><%= f.label :URL %></p>
          <p><input type="url" name="url" placeholder="Heroku URL"/></p>
          <input type="submit" class="round button" value="Register" />
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
<div style="margin:1em 0; height:40px;clear:both;"><br></div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="twelve columns panel callout">
    <h2>Your output will go here...</h2>
    <h5>
        <p>
      When you are finished this assignment, your app will display links to class Heroku web sites here. 
      Go to the <a href="http://polar-journey-7101.herokuapp.com">example</a> to see how your
      page should behave. 
      </p>
      <p>Register your own site into your Registry.</p>
    </h5>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <h4>Registered Links</h4>
    <table style="width:100%">
        <tr>
            <th>Course</th>
            <th>Student ID</th>
            <th>URL</th>
        </tr>
        <% @students.each do |student| %>
            <% student.urls.each do |studentURL| %>
                <tr>
                    <td><%= student.name %></td>
                    <td><%= student.course %></td>
                    <td><a href="<%= studentURL.url %>"><%= studentURL.url %></a></td>
                </tr>
            <% end %>
        <% end %>
    </table>
</div>
